  "title": "Quantity Surveyor (Civil Engineering)",
  "description": "<h5>Job Description &amp; Requirements</h5>\n<p>1. Preparation of tender   submission.</p>\n<p>2. Taking off quantities and   measurement.</p>\n<p>3. Requesting for   quotations/proposals.</p>\n<p>4. Assist to prepare early   stage budgets and detailed cost plans.</p>\n<p>5. Assist in procurement and   negotiation of price with suppliers and sub-contractors.</p>\n<p>6. Site visits, assessments   and projection for on-going projects and future work.</p>\n<p>7. Assess and submit monthly   progress claim, and recommend subcontractor's monthly progress payment.</p>\n<p>8. Work independently.</p>\n<p>Job Requirements:</p>\n<p>1. Diploma In Civil   Engineering</p>\n<p>2. Qualification or experience   for Civil Engineering, External Work</p>\n<p>3. At least 3 to 5 years of   relevant experience</p>\n<p>4. Good working attitude and   willing to learn</p>\n<p>5. Knowledge in AutoCAD</p>",
